Company Overview of Universal Hospital Services Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Universal Hospital Services, Inc. provides health care technology management and service solutions to the health care industry in the United States. The company operates through three segments: Medical Equipment Solutions (MES), Clinical Engineering Solutions (CES), and Surgical Services (SS). The MES segment provides medical equipment outsourcing services, including patient-ready medical equipment on a supplemental or peak needs basis; and daily, monthly, or pay-per-use basis through its 83 district service centers, as well as medical equipment through tailored equipment agreement solutions. It also offers on-site managed solutions; provides single use disposable items; and sells and distri...
Universal Hospital Services, Inc. provides health care technology management and service solutions to the health care industry in the United States. The company operates through three segments: Medical Equipment Solutions (MES), Clinical Engineering Solutions (CES), and Surgical Services (SS). The MES segment provides medical equipment outsourcing services, including patient-ready medical equipment on a supplemental or peak needs basis; and daily, monthly, or pay-per-use basis through its 83 district service centers, as well as medical equipment through tailored equipment agreement solutions. It also offers on-site managed solutions; provides single use disposable items; and sells and distributes specialty medical equipment. In addition, this segment buys, sources, remarkets, and disposes pre-owned medical equipment. The CES segment offers inspection, preventative maintenance, repair, logistics, and consulting services. Its services include fee-for-service arrangements, scheduled maintenance and inspection services, full service maintenance, inspection and repair services, and vendor management services; full and part-time, on-site, and resident-based equipment maintenance solutions; and medical technology consulting and advisory solutions. The SS segment provides surgical equipment and associated products, which include supplemental or peak needs mobile surgical equipment solutions; and disposable products and/or ancillary equipment. Universal Hospital Services, Inc. serves national, regional, and local acute care hospitals; and alternate site providers through direct sales force and Websites, including uhs.com, UHSSurgicalServices.com, and OnCareMedical.com. The company was founded in 1939 and is based in Minneapolis, Minnesota. Universal Hospital Services, Inc. is a subsidiary of UHS Holdco, Inc.
