Universal Hospital Services Inc. Key Developments

Universal Hospital Services Inc. Reports Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended March 31, 2017; Reaffirms Earnings Guidance for the Full Year of 2017
May 8 17
Universal Hospital Services Inc. reported earnings results for the first quarter ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company’s total revenues were $130.7 million, representing a $8.6 million or 7.0% increase from total revenues of $122.1 million for the same period of 2016. Adjusted EBITDA for the three months ended March 31, 2017, was $34.6 million, a $3.8 million or 12.3% increase from adjusted EBITDA of $30.8 million for the same period of 2016. Net loss attributable to the company was $2.0 million compared to $4.7 million a year ago.


The company reaffirmed its earnings guidance for the full year of 2017. For the period the company expects adjusted EBITDA of $135 million to $140 million and accrual capex of $55 million to $65 million.


Universal Hospital Seeks Acquisitions
May 8 17
Universal Hospital Services Inc. is seeking acquisitions. Based on the level of operating performance expected in 2017, the company believes that their cash from operations and additional borrowings under senior secured credit facility will meet their liquidity needs for the foreseeable future, exclusive of any borrowings that it may make to finance potential acquisitions.



