About Our Leaders














 75+ Years of Experience











 1939
FOUNDED
ABC Oxygen Tent Rental Service founded in Minneapolis. 





 1941
ACQUISITION
Ed Fish and his mom, Clara Fish, purchase the business. They run the company with with a simple plan; provide oxygen tents to area hospitals to treat patients suffering from respiratory illness. 





 1969
NAME CHANGE
The company is renamed from ABC Oxygen Tent Rental Service to Universal Hospital Services, Inc. 





 1980
COMPANY EXPANSION
Clinical Engineering Services added to provide supplemental biomedical services and outsourced clinical engineering programs for customers.





 1990
COMPANY EXPANSION
Specialty beds and therapy surfaces added to rental portfolio. Equipment sales added for new and used equipment.





 2011
COMPANY EXPANSION
Surgical Services added.
Surgical equipment and technician services added and expanded to become one of the leading Surgical Services providers in the U.S.





 2017
Continued growth
Today UHS owns or manages more than 700,000 units of medical equipment for more than 7,000 national, regional and local acute care hospitals and alternate site providers across the U.S.











































