Why Choose UHS




UHS: Passion for Patient Care

Passion for patient care has found a home at UHS.
At UHS, find a place to work where your passion for service and patient care can thrive. We continually nurture talent, reward achievement and champion personal growth because these all drive our passion for service. If you are an innovative, driven and passionate individual who sees value in supporting caregivers and patients, join us. 












We manage
700,000
Pieces OF MEDICAL EQUIPMENT






We work with
7,000+
Acute Care Hospitals & Alternate Site Providers






We are located in
80+
District Offices throughout the U.S






We've spent the last
75+
Years Proudly Serving the Healthcare Industry

















Build Your Future

Make UHS your home for learning and growing. Find your place in our culture of caring and we’ll build a better future together. 











We Recognize Hard Work
Your efforts are meaningful and won’t go unnoticed. We recognize skill and hard work with incentive-based awards, employee spotlight awards and an annual employee recognition program. 












Grow Your Skills
Take advantage of opportunities to grow: tuition reimbursement, student internships, career pathing and mentorship programs. We all grow when we each grow. 












Community Service
Our passion for serving finds its way to the communities where we live. From providing much-needed equipment for natural disasters, or getting involved in local health care charities —we continue to look for ways to provide our services in the areas where we work and live. 












Shared Pride
Every day UHS employees positively impact patients and take an active role in health care. Making a difference—every single day, with every single patient—is a source of pride for the entire UHS family.












Commitment to Diversity
UHS employs a diverse workforce of individuals to bring distinct perspectives to each area of our business. This approach fosters an environment of continuous improvement and allows our employees to thrive in their roles supporting our health care clients.












Equal Opportunity Employment
UHS provides equal employment opportunities to all employees and applicants for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender, sexual orientation, national origin, age, physical or mental disability, genetic information, marital status, status as a disabled veteran, veteran of the Vietnam era, recently separated veteran or other protected veteran or any other characteristic protected by applicable federal, state or local law, UHS complies with all applicable laws governing nondiscrimination in employment for each of its work locations







